Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters, which substitutes for the bank's telephone number, has increased.
This is reported by Kommersant with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator gave the communication operators information about more than 2,500 numbers from which they called clients of various financial institutions.
In 189 cases, operators found a substitution of the number.
Another 218 numbers blocked, and in 59 cases established a restriction on the use of financial services.
Deputy Head of the Central Bank Information Security Department Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced the replacement of the issue.
He explained that the operators do not always respond to the warnings of the Central Bank about fraudulent calls, citing the lack of such obligation in the law "On Communications."
In the bank "Otkritie," Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with a substitution of numbers.
According to the press service of Beeline, some of the information about fraudulent calls, which was handed over to the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to malfunctions in the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of numbers of fraudsters, to which the operator will contact with each call to check the number.
He explained that in order to create such a base, it will be necessary to amend the legislation.
