Regions offered to share the secrets of business support
As it became known to the "Parliamentskaya Gazeta," on September 27, Andrei Kutepov, Chairman of the Committee of the Federation Council for Economic Policy, sent a letter to the Minister of Economic Development Maxim Oreshkin and Finance Minister Anton Siluanov with a proposal to express his position regarding the initiatives of the subjects of the Federation to improve the legislation in the field of support of small and medium-sized businesses (SMEs).
It is time to establish interregional relations
The Committee of the Federation Council for Economic Policy summarized the information received from the regions about the existing programs of business development and the legalization of self-employed, as well as the results of such programs.
In their letters, the regions told the senators about the problems of SME development and sent proposals to improve the current legislation.
"To date, communication between the regions is insufficiently established, as a result of which the entrepreneurial community in all regions of the senators was outlined the question of the lack of information about regional programs of development of entrepreneurship in the whole country," said Andrey Kutepov.
In the appendix to the letter sent to the Government, he presented a set of positive developments in the regions for the legalization of self-employment and summary data from the regions with proposals and problems (it is available to the editorial office).
In addition to relevant ministries, consolidated data from the regions are also sent to the heads of regional executive bodies.
The exchange of information on the positively implemented achievements in the regions could give impetus to the development of entrepreneurship as a whole.
The first step to this exchange will be the direction of information available to the Committee for Economic Policy," Senator said to the "Parliamentskaya Gazeta."
Useful experience
Today, in many regions of the country, programs for support of small and medium-sized businesses have been adopted and successfully implemented.
For example, the Vologda region operates the Center for Support of Entrepreneurship, which, in addition to financial support measures, assists businessmen in the certification of finished products.
In the Ivanovo region, a business support system has been developed, providing for the implementation of the principle of one window through multifunctional centers.
In the Krasnodar region, beginner agricultural consumer cooperatives provide grants at the expense of the regional budget.
The center of cluster development operates in the Orel region.
The Amur region within the framework of the federal project "Accleration of small and medium-sized businesses" provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators, created on the basis of existing non-state co-working centers, at the expense of the federal budget.
And in some other regions special measures are taken to support youth entrepreneurship.
Self-employed continue to be removed from the shadows
According to the regional authorities, a number of changes in the current legislation should be made to support small and medium-sized businesses more effectively.
For example, the Arkhangelsk region proposed to replace the term "self-employment" with "entrepreneurial activity," since this "is the most consistent with the content of the state service to promote self-employment of unemployed citizens."
In the Ivanovo region it is necessary to make amendments that provide for the expansion of the list of activities provided by self-employed citizens, including activities for the finishing and repair of residential premises, summer houses, physical training.
The Bryansk region considers it important to strengthen control over unscrupulous producers of dairy products with the help of the veterinary system "Mercury."
And in the Kostroma and Magadan regions advocate for consolidation in the legal field of the concept of "social entrepreneurship" and directions of support of social entrepreneurship.
All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills.
"All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized businesses, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills," assured Andrey Kutepov.
