A series of pickets began on September 18 in support of Ustinov himself and since then continues every day.
Currently, the participants of the action, replacing each other, stand, holding a poster with the inscription "Freedom to All" and the names of convicted and arrested after uncoordinated meetings in Moscow in the summer of 2019.
In addition to Ustinov, on the poster the names of Yegor Zhukov, Kirill Zhukov, Danil Beglets, Yevgeny Kovalenko, Konstantin Kotov, Ivan Podkopaev, Aidar Gubaidulina, Alexei Minyaylo, Sergei Fomin, Samariddin Rajabov, Nikita Chirtsova, Eduard Malyshevsky, Vladislav Sinitsa.
On September 16, the Tverskoy Court of Moscow sentenced 24 years old Ustinov to 3.5 years in a penal colony on charges of violence against a fighter of the OMON Rosgvardiy on an uncoordinated action on August 3 in the center of Moscow (Article 318 Part 2 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
After that, on September 20, at the request of the Prosecutor General's Office, the court changed Ustinov's measure of restraint from being detained for non-exit.
Thus, the petition for the liberation of Ustinov collected more than 112 thousand signatures per day.
Theatre and cinema artists started a flash mob in support of their colleague.
To participate in a single picket in solidarity with the actor on September 18 on the Old Square line lined up.
Human rights activists, journalists, scientists, teachers, doctors, Orthodox priests demanded the re-sight of the case.
As Ustinova's sister Yulia told Interfax, her brother does not plan to speak at a meeting on September 29 in the capital in support of the defendants of the "Moscow case."
Supplies of "sanctions" to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government calculated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from the countries that fell under the Russian food embargo has decreased more than 100 times since 2013.
According to a report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from the sanctioned countries in the first half of 2019 against 3,422.2 thousand tons in the same period of 2013, Interfax reports.
At the same time, the value of imported products declined to $226.5mn from $4bn 975.5mn respectively.
We are talking about the supply of goods that did not fall under the embargo.
According to the report, the volume of prohibited products was compensated by increasing imports from imports from the CIS, Africa, Southeast Asia, Serbia.
Recall that in late August, the government prolonged until December 31, 2020 the validity of the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited for import into Russia in the framework of countersanctions.
The document, posted on the official portal of legal information, noted that the validity of the rules for another year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the decision to destroy the sanctions was applied to products from the USA, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, from August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein, from January 1, 2016 - Ukraine joined this list.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of the illegally imported "sanctions" (products caught under the food embargo, which Moscow introduced in response to the anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government allowed to destroy "sanctions" food in any legal way.
As the sanctions of the West remain, Russia has also prolonged its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, the products that citizens import for personal use, this measure does not apply.
The ban does not apply to the importation of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, Mikhail Fedotov, head of the Presidential Council for the Development of Civil Society and Human Rights, described the destruction of food as "just immoral" as "just immoral", and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, Rospotrebnadzor launched an initiative to ban the destruction of food suitable for use in early June.
After that, a similar recommendation was given to the government by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
Deputy Prime Minister Alexei Gordeev said that it is wrong to destroy food, and we need to think how to use them for their appointment, assessing the quality.
The head of the firm was found guilty of tax evasion
Vyacheslav Morozov, Director of "Land and Law" LLC, was found guilty of committing crimes under Part 2 of Article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (evasion of taxes from the organization by inclusion in the tax declaration of deliberately false information committed in a particularly large amount) and Part 2 of Article 327 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (defamation of the official purpose of his/her application.
It is reported by the press service of the Investigative Directorate of the TFR in Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009 Vyacheslav Morozov introduced information about imperfect transactions to the tax accounting documents of LLC.
According to the fictitious documents, the company suffered additional costs, and, therefore, the amount of taxes on added value and the profits of the organization 11.2 million rubles were reduced.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years in prison.
By 2023, the first school of a new format will be opened in the center of the capital
The school of the new model will be opened in Khamovniki.
According to the head of Moskomstroyinvest Anastasia Pyatova, there will create all the conditions for self-realization and development of talents of children.
The educational institution decided to call "New Look."
This project will be supervised by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Foundation "Economic Development of Higher School."
The design of the building with an area of about 10 thousand "squares" are planned to start next year.
The construction works will be finished at the end of 2022, and the next one will be recruited by the first students.
"The project provides for the creation of a public, non-commercial educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental methods," - noted in the press service of Moskomstroyinvest.
In Chile began to build a telescope worth 1 billion euros
This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
According to ESO, this week officially began the construction of the dome of the building, where the telescope E-ELT (European Extremely Large Telescope - "European ultra-large telescope"), while the most expensive and ambitious ground astronomical project will be located.
Its total value, according to ESO estimates, will exceed a billion euros.
Most of this money will be spent on the manufacture of equipment and construction of the observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope - its record large mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments of 1.4 meters.
This is a huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflective surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters will help E-ELT get the first detailed photos of planets outside the Solar System, stars in other galaxies, as well as look for doubles of the Earth.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory for observation of the surroundings Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole in the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome is only started, mirrors, scientific tools and other components of the observatory scientists, engineers and other specialists have been developing for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, whose total value was about 400 million euros, received the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
